Something feels terribly wrong here. The thick air seems to actively drain all sound and light from the forest, filling it with a quiet, perpetual dimness. This silent, brooding darkness emanates an impending sense of danger. As you look ahead for signs of this danger you spot something through the trees that makes the hairs on the back of your neck rise - dozens of warped and twisted grave markers line the ground. They look old, very old, but the ground they rest on looks like recently disturbed....
